alvarionTextualConventions.name: alvarionTextualConventions
alvarionTextualConventions.contactinfo: Alvarion Ltd. Postal: 21a HaBarzel St. P.O. Box 13139 Tel-Aviv 69710 Israel Phone: +972 3 645 6262
alvarionTextualConventions.description: This module defines the Textual Conventions used in Alvarion enterprise MIBs.

AlvarionAuthenticationMode.name: AlvarionAuthenticationMode
AlvarionAuthenticationMode.description: Specifies the authentication mode to be used. local: The authentication is done locally from the device local database information. profile: An AAA profile is used in order to retrieve the authentication parameters.

AlvarionUsersAuthenticationMode.name: AlvarionUsersAuthenticationMode
AlvarionUsersAuthenticationMode.description: Specifies the authentication mode to be used. none: Users are not allowed to login. local: The authentication is done locally from the device local database information. profile: An AAA profile is used in order to retrieve the authentication parameters. localAndProfile: The authentication is done locally first. If it fails an AAA profile is used.

AlvarionUsersAuthenticationType.name: AlvarionUsersAuthenticationType
AlvarionUsersAuthenticationType.description: Specifies the authentication type to be used. mac: Users authenticated using their MAC addresses. ieee802dot1x: Users authenticated through 802.1x. html: Users authenticated with html.

AlvarionNotificationEnable.name: AlvarionNotificationEnable
AlvarionNotificationEnable.description: Specifies the generation of notification traps. enable: Enable the generation of the associated notification. disable: Disables the generation of the associated notification

AlvarionProfileIndex.name: AlvarionProfileIndex
AlvarionProfileIndex.description: A profile index refers to an entry in the AAA profile table.

AlvarionProfileIndexOrZero.name: AlvarionProfileIndexOrZero
AlvarionProfileIndexOrZero.description: A profile index refers to an entry in the AAA profile table. When the special value Zero is specified, no AAA server profile is selected.

AlvarionServerIndex.name: AlvarionServerIndex
AlvarionServerIndex.description: A server index refers to an entry in the AAA server table.

AlvarionServerIndexOrZero.name: AlvarionServerIndexOrZero
AlvarionServerIndexOrZero.description: A server index refers to an entry in the AAA server table. When the special value Zero is specified, no AAA server is selected.

AlvarionSSID.name: AlvarionSSID
AlvarionSSID.description: A generic service set identifier (SSID) convention is defined here and used throughout the Alvarion proprietary MIBs. This specific textual convention is used for inputing SSIDs.

AlvarionSSIDOrNone.name: AlvarionSSIDOrNone
AlvarionSSIDOrNone.description: A generic service set identifier (SSID) convention is defined here and used throughout the Alvarion proprietary MIBs. This specific textual convention is used when displaying SSIDs.

AlvarionSecurity.name: AlvarionSecurity
AlvarionSecurity.description: An enumeration of the different Security modes allowed in the Alvarion products. NOTE: 'unknown'- Could not identify the protection mode. 'none' - No wireless protection. 'wep' - WEP (static keys). 'ieee802dot1x' - 802.1x no encryption. 'ieee802dot1xWithWep' - 802.1x + WEP (dynamic keys). 'wpa' - 802.1x + TKIP + Key source AAA profile. 'wpaPsk' - 802.1x + TKIP + Key Source Pre-Shared Key.

AlvarionPriorityQueue.name: AlvarionPriorityQueue
AlvarionPriorityQueue.description: An enumeration of the different queues supported in the QOS and Bandwidth control feature of the Alvarion products.

AlvarionDataRate.name: AlvarionDataRate
AlvarionDataRate.description: An enumeration of the different data rates supported on a per VAP basis.

AlvarionRadioType.name: AlvarionRadioType
AlvarionRadioType.description: An enumeration of the different radio types used in the Alvarion products.
